    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A technique of pottery surface treatment in which an implement is pressed into wet clay using a rocking motion. Varied patterns may be achieved depending on the form of the tool, and direction or spacing of impressions.</Note_Text>
